subSubSection.paragraph:
Apex of last visible abdominal sternite (
VII
) in male subtruncate or faintly concave, with one pair of marginal setae, in female rounded and with two pairs of marginal setae.

Median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs. 40 & 41
) in lateral view almost straight in basal two-thirds and slightly curved ventrally in apical third, in dorsal view slightly sinuate, with apical portion curved to the right; its ventral side edged laterally in apical part and depressed between margins; terminal lamella in dorsal view wide and long, concave, rounded at apex, in lateral view thin, slightly bent ventrally just at apex. Apical orifice in dorsal position, wide apically. Internal sac with spiny formations and a small spine in apical portion of median lobe.

Female genitalia (
Figs. 42 & 43
): gonocoxite narrow in ventral view and comparatively long, about 0.8 times as long as gonosubcoxite, with narrow base.
